summary: Used automotive vehicle retailer Carmax (NYSE:KMX) reported Q4 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 6.9% year on year to $5.79 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.43 per share was 36.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
